Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.87,0:00:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything else.\NNothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.51,0:00:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All comes into existence by divine\Nordination.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.32,0:00:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing expresses the fulfillment of\Nits essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.35,0:00:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In the unfolding, everything is at its\Nstate of perfection at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.76,0:00:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a perfect flower unfolding.\NIt is still a perfect flower unfolding
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.84,0:00:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,perfectly. Still unfolding perfectly.\NSo you've received the perfection of all
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of creation.\NWhen you see the perfection of all of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.92,0:00:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,creation,\Nyou see that the criminal is being the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.48,0:01:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect criminal as he goes bang.\NHe is the perfect criminal, is he not?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.68,0:01:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be it and say, "Oh, but\Nshouldn't this world be peaceful without
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.43,0:01:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,criminals?"\NBut then what would you do without
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.40,0:01:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,criminals?\N>> You'd have to create a whole another
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.52,0:01:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,world in which there's lots of criminals\Nand horrible people and stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.79,0:01:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't you?\NIf the purpose of the world is an
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.04,0:01:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite\Nchoices, if it's sort of a purgatorial
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.40,0:01:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,paradise,\Nif you destroy the quality of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.72,0:01:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of it is, you'd have to go create a\Nwhole another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.47,0:01:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Where can you walk into a hail of\Nbullets unless there's the war? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.39,0:02:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you learn to forgive if there\Nwere nothing to forgive? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.07,0:02:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, as the mira course of\Nmiracles points out, once you see it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.28,0:02:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly, there is nothing to forgive.\NAnd that dissolves the whole issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.84,0:02:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to eat those flower\Npetals. I'll eat them. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.08,0:02:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The personality I grew up with was\Naesthetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.28,0:02:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Aesthetic. Introvert.\NIntrovert. Aesthetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.56,0:02:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ectomorph.\NEctomorphs are thin and nervous. Don't
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.76,0:02:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,eat much.\Nand they shut off the lights all the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.72,0:02:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,time. Save electric.\NPeople visit you and say, "Look, I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.59,0:02:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,brought you lunch." You say, "I don't\Nneed lunch. I've got a banana in the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.16,0:02:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,refrigerator.\NThat's enough till tomorrow, isn't it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.51,0:03:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, h\NI wanted to complete what we were
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.40,0:03:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about this morning.\Nthat you know all that needs to be known
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.51,0:03:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for the whole way\Nbecause you may consider yourself even a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.23,0:03:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,beginner\Nand find yourself suddenly and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.15,0:03:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,unexpectedly at the final door. Can\Nhappen just like that and it can happen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.04,0:03:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,happen from the pits of hell.\NYou went to a couple lectures, somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.23,0:03:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,told you way to meditate. Next thing you\Nknow,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.68,0:03:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there you are.\NIt's never too soon to be prepared
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because the doorway opens and if you\Nfail it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.84,0:04:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequence is rather severe. May\Ntake many a lifetime to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.64,0:04:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,One was presented with the opportunity\Nof being at one with God and once
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.51,0:04:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,said no to it.\NIt's crushing crushing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore\Nto know
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what you need to know.\NHe would say why tell us this early in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the game. It's not early in the game.\NIt's not early in the game for anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.40,0:04:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,here.\NNobody was early in the game would even
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.91,0:04:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,be here.\NWould scare the pants off of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.44,0:04:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I open all my books with a\Ndedication Gloria and excelsius deal. If
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.84,0:04:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get past that page,\Nthen the book's for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:05:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And sort of a qualifier.\NGlory and exaltious deal. My god, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.36,0:05:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this guy? Some kind of a weirdo?\NTake this book away, Genevieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.91,0:05:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, only so I already have a guard at\Nthe beginning of the book. See,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.63,0:05:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and also a caveat.\NThose who are spiritually timid
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.75,0:05:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or committed to some rigid religion\Nmight be well upset by the contents of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what follows and it would be advisable\Nfor them not to read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.80,0:05:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Although many of the things could be\Nconsidered conflictual, I think we've
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.68,0:05:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualized them in such a way that\Nthey are not conflictual. You
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.08,0:05:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,understand? And we just discovering that\Nthere's multiple heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.40,0:06:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So all you have to do is change the word\Nexclusive and you're okay with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody.\NAll right? So there comes a time when
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.91,0:06:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,one is confronted\Nwith the knowingness. With the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.80,0:06:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness it's all non-verbal.\NThe higher demands are all nonverbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody there. There's no words.\NThere's no concepts. But there is a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.31,0:06:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness.\NAnd up comes the knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.96,0:06:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The last and final step is facing you.\NAnd the requirement
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.08,0:06:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is to die. H that is the requirement.\NUnless the fear of absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.80,0:06:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,death arises, that isn't the final door\Nbecause you still have hope left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.24,0:07:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But when that is eliminated, then\Nthere's no way out and one is confronted
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.63,0:07:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with\Nthe absoluteness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The things that come that are operative\Nat that point
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the energy field of the teacher\Nin whom you have great faith. It tells
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.03,0:07:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you how to walk through that because\Nthat teacher has walked through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the conviction of the truth\Nof the inner experience
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very firm\Nrock-like and you feel its
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,rock-likeness.\NIt was rock-like
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.96,0:07:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that knowingness still because few go\Nthrough everyone is going through leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.80,0:07:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that conviction there.\NThere's that rocklike knowingness to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.68,0:07:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,walk through all fear no matter what.\NBut the fear is quite intense
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.52,0:08:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is death.\NIt is death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.56,0:08:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And something else is needed\Nwithin yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.00,0:08:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,already exists\Nthat which is willing to lay down its
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.63,0:08:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,life for God.\NThat's not something you acquire,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.00,0:08:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,something you have to develop.\NIt's something you locate within
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself\Nbecause that question will come up over
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.75,0:08:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and over again in the spiritual pathway.\NAm I willing to surrender this to God?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.24,0:08:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I willing to surrender that to God?\NAnd you will then locate within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.36,0:08:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is a capacity to lay anything\Ndown for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.80,0:08:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If Krishna Buddha Jesus stood here and\Nsaid, "Would you lay down your life for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.44,0:09:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,me?"\NYou would say, "Yes, oh Lord." Do you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.44,0:09:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,find within yourself\Nthat which would say yes, oh Lord, to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.24,0:09:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that request?\NIf you do that, you will finesse that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness from yourself\Nbecause it is already within the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.08,0:09:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wise to come to know that within\Nyourself to know that it's there and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.39,0:09:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can call upon it because now at\Nthe final door you have the profound
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.08,0:09:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,strength and conviction. That is\Nstrength.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.60,0:09:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The strength of the truth of God\Naffirmed by those who have walked
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.12,0:09:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,through it.\NThat's the pathway of non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.04,0:09:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nbut then combined with it is the power
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.51,0:10:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of devotion.\NSo the heart and the mind are one at
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.24,0:10:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that point.\NThe devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.80,0:10:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that within you which is willing to lay\Ndown its life for God,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.00,0:10:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,locate that within yourself. Now\Nwhen you don't need it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.32,0:10:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because the final moment arises\Nunannounced,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.48,0:10:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,unannounced.\NNo way of knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.95,0:10:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, quite unexpected.\NYou're driving down the highway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.92,0:10:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly you see the come car coming at\Nyou. There's a loud screaming metal. You
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.56,0:10:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,feel an agonizing pain in the your neck\Nas your neck breaks
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.32,0:10:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you. There's the moment right there. It\Njust opened itself. Unexpected,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.83,0:11:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,unprepared for.\NNobody said meditate for the next 3
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.68,0:11:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,hours. It's going to arrive at noon.\NYou're on your way to pick up the kids
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.12,0:11:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from school.\NUnexpected suddenness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear of a new meditative technique,\Nyou thought that sounds kinky. I think
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.07,0:11:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try it.\NAnja buuja buuja anjabuja anabuja. And
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.76,0:11:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all of a sudden it opens up. It's just\Nso there's no warning. That's why I tell
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.07,0:11:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you now early in the game. It's not\Nreally it's late in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.88,0:11:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Delayed. I should have told you the\Nfirst lecture, but I thought my sc
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.24,0:11:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,would have scared everybody out. Yeah, I\Nbetter save that for number 12. You know
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.39,0:11:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what I mean? But you're going to have to\Ndie in the end. No, no, I signed up for
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.72,0:12:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that course.\NThat's what the feeling is. Because the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.63,0:12:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ego is stronger, it's it defies\Neverything. The ego is just unbelievable
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the tricks and the and it's learned this\Nover you know huge expanses speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.07,0:12:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,from a temporal perceptual viewpoint\Nit's learned it over huge expanses of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.51,0:12:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,time how to survive\Nand now
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it faces extin extinction\Nin this particular consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.44,0:12:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it struggles for survival Without\Nme, you will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.68,0:12:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it's going to tell you.\NWithout me, I am your life. I am the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.04,0:12:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,source of your life.\NI'm the core of your existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.60,0:13:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender me and you're dead.\NAnd there's where you need the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.76,0:13:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,conviction.\NYou reach within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For thee, oh Lord, do I lay down my life\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.88,0:13:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you summon forth the very core\Nof devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is within you already\Nthat which loves God more than the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,personal self.\NIt already exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.83,0:13:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you summon it forth.\NSo the power of devotion is the pathway
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.51,0:13:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the uh the pathway of devotion the\Npathway of non-duality
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.00,0:13:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pathway of service to others as\Nyou saw all these people come up that it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:14:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is their joy to serve you just it is my\Njoy to serve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.19,0:14:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings me in ecstatic state which I\Ncan't allow to develop
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,or this talk will end.\NI tried to stay away from the devotional
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.39,0:14:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and cuz it brings all of it to a close.\NAll right, we wanted to answer some
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.16,0:14:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,questions now today.\NUm, and I do want to thank all the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.72,0:14:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,people who work round the clock 7 days a\Nweek who call you or you can call them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.39,0:14:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at any time who will drop everything and\Ndo anything for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.76,0:14:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And they may seem like trivial things,\Nbut when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.68,0:14:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in need need of an espresso, you need an\Nespresso.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.88,0:15:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some very funny questions here.\NI don't understand that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand that one either.\NAll right. So, somebody asked about the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.60,0:15:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,course of miracles. You know, there's a\Nnumber of pathways. All of them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.32,0:15:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,terrific.\NThe 12 steps are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, to reach enlightenment, all you\Nneed is step three and step 11. And the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.12,0:15:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,12 step course. Third step is\Nwillingness to surrender your life to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.56,0:15:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,God. And the 11th step is sought through\Nprayer and meditation to ask God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.16,0:15:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for me. Those two is all you need the\Nwhole way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two will suffice. There's only\Nabout the course of miracles we said to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate around 600. It comes from I\Nthink what would be called celestial
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.39,0:16:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,realms.\NUh probably about the same level as uh
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.68,0:16:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the white brotherhood. And uh so the\Nhigher celestial realms have contact
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.68,0:16:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with humans\Nspecial arrangements usually a karmic uh
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.24,0:16:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment and agreement.\NThe only thing the only thing that I
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.92,0:16:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,object to in the course of miracles is\Nthe one is the one lesson
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.68,0:16:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,uh trust your brother\Nthat has to be taken with a proviso.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.75,0:16:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard what I said this morning.\N>> Trust your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.39,0:16:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's true in the celestial\Nrealm. I don't think it's too trustable
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.19,0:16:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in this realm. That one has to be\Nmodified for this world. Yes, that's the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.83,0:16:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,only error in it. You know, of course,\Nthe miracle didn't calary to thousand,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.68,0:16:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,calary to 600. So, you know, it's not\Nall that can be said about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.92,0:16:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Because the downside of the\Nlovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.75,0:17:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is that um\Nnot being able or willing or the two
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.88,0:17:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,together to see that the tiger if\Nprovoked can still kill you, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.95,0:17:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and to still love the person despite\Nthat. despite that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.03,0:17:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'd say trust your brother\Nand keep an eye on HIM
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.79,0:17:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,on a certain level. However, it is true\Nthat people will rise to be
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.52,0:17:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you see them as\Npeople will rise to the expectation. So
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.64,0:17:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on a certain level it is true and on the\Nhighest level of course it's true
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.44,0:17:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't make any sense.\NThere's no me to trust and no you to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.84,0:18:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,trust because that is\Nviewing separation as a reality. There
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is no me that trusts you because there's\Nonly the one self. So the course is that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.72,0:18:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the only quiggly part I would say\Nabout the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.64,0:18:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to stand up all this time. I'm\Ngoing to fall down here in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.00,0:18:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's cuz I have to read. I can't do\Ntwo things at once. Stand up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.67,0:18:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and read. I can sit down and read or I\Ncan stand up. But to stand up and read
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.72,0:18:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is difficult. Oh my goodness. All right,\NI better start talking fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.24,0:18:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nall that I teach is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.79,0:18:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential.\NNothing that I teach is from elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.52,0:19:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,other than that which I quote as being\Nfrom elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.28,0:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\NI have permission to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.00,0:19:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. The answer is yes. Resist. Okay.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.84,0:19:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the conviction, the conviction then the\Npower, the vibration of a teacher who
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.72,0:19:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,has experienced it the whole way is\Nand that it is the absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.12,0:19:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,subjectivity\Nof self-realization. See
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.36,0:19:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,self-realization\Nwhich is another term one might use
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.32,0:19:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is radically subjective.\NIt is radical subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.96,0:20:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of the truth of the\Nmystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.96,0:20:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth of God imminent\Nrather than transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.44,0:20:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystic is the one who experiences\Nthe reality of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.64,0:20:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as the core and the essence of life,\Nthe core and essence of one's existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.55,0:20:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one's creation\Nand the reality of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.84,0:20:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It reveals itself\Nand that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.15,0:20:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,brings about the absoluteness\Nof the certainty
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.96,0:20:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the source of the vibrational\Nfrequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.84,0:20:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The so-called grace of the guru is\Nnothing but
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.76,0:20:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the vibrational frequency of the\Nabsolute certainty
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.88,0:21:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is that absolute certainty\Nthat is needed at the great and final
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.91,0:21:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,moment\Nthe guru that you picture at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.48,0:21:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It better not calibrate 180. I'll\Ntruth goes for a big voice boy ain't
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.24,0:21:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,going to give it away.\N>> So all right. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.60,0:21:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I think we've already explained um\Nactually with all these questions here
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.03,0:21:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we've already explained them all. Only\Nyou don't realize that we've explained
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.55,0:21:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,them all.\NNow we really need this calibrated scale
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.32,0:21:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness again to answer some of\Nthese questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.48,0:21:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nas we said the numeric scale is not a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.15,0:22:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,better than scale.\NIt's each each level is perfect for its
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.84,0:22:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,assignment.\NThe scale below it would be deficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.96,0:22:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the scale above it would not even make\Nit attractive or interesting. So it has
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.91,0:22:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to be something to do your excellent\Nbest
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.64,0:22:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be at that which you are\Ncalibrated for. Now the movement of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.15,0:22:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,level through the levels of calibrations\Nhas to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.44,0:22:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual realization and work and the\Nevolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.91,0:22:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is potentiated by your own\Ncommitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.60,0:22:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual pathway is really a way of\Ncontextualizing your life. It's not a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.15,0:22:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,matter of where anyone is on a scale.\NBesides, as I've told you,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.60,0:23:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the doorway can open at any time.\NYou think, well, I got to go through all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.28,0:23:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this here. I ain't even in bliss yet.\NHow could I get enlightened?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.88,0:23:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can go from here all the way\Nto there. Tenth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.60,0:23:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a tenth of a second.\NIt was an eternity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.96,0:23:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of agony.\NEons.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.20,0:23:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The lower depths of hell are like the\Nhigher levels beyond all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.32,0:23:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Alwayness. The alwaysness.\NThe unendingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.48,0:23:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the agony is forever\Nand there is no hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.91,0:24:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And all last vestages of hope are\Nremoved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.48,0:24:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you know you're in for the real\Nagony.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.64,0:24:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,After an eon or so,\Nsuddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.72,0:24:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the door opens.\NJust don't think just cuz you're in hell
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.55,0:24:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that it can't happen.\NMoments of hell, moments of agony,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.52,0:24:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,moments of doubt, moments of anger. The\Ndoorway can open at any time. All the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work that you do then prepares\Nfor the final pathway
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.88,0:24:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,happily.\NUsually it is more gradual person
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.55,0:24:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes more and more loving more and\Nmore forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.08,0:25:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,uh usually it's rather gradual\Nand those states also as I pointed out
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.00,0:25:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,have their vulnerability\Nin the 500s one's vulnerability is one's
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.67,0:25:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,naive\Nyou can be blissed out in a very high
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.96,0:25:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,state and then also\Nget hit by that which is non integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.00,0:25:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is in an unprepared area and crashed\Ndown again and now it's horrible because
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.60,0:25:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you've been in a higher state.\NAll right. So, nevertheless, the karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.67,0:25:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,merit that you have earned through\Ncommitment and devotion to spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.20,0:25:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,inner work etc.\NIt comes to your rescue
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.24,0:26:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,happily.\NThe way through then is is straight to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.67,0:26:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,face whatever is coming up. Surrender it\Nto God. Surrender up your reservations
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.72,0:26:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about it.\NWhatever is required. The way is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.64,0:26:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,straight through. And as you get to each\Nlevel, each level is capped by a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.55,0:26:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration.\NEach level feels good as you emerge into
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.40,0:26:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NBut then as you float up through that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.67,0:26:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,level,\Nthe reason that 500 is not 600 is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.12,0:26:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,between 500 and 600\Nthere's dualities
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.91,0:26:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,holding you into that position.\NSo on the one hand it feels incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.20,0:26:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The move from here to here, each move up\Nis incredible. But each each level
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.60,0:27:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,itself then represents a limitation of\Nthat which is beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.08,0:27:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think\Na great guru at a thousand
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.60,0:27:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is marvelous to the viewpoint of a\Npopulace where 85% is below even
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.32,0:27:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,contemporary\Nas compared to the possibilities of the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.36,0:27:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual universe. It's probably\Nkindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.15,0:27:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And is that\Nwhatever my awareness might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.84,0:27:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's of a kindergarten level to\Nhigher energies. You know, when we say
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.36,0:27:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,an archangel is 50,000 and over,\Nwhat could we possibly be? Even if in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.36,0:27:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the so in the view of other people who\Nare not as evolved the college education
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.52,0:27:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,seems you know pretty impressive but to\Na postd doctoral researcher
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.08,0:28:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,doctor 8 is just you know jacks for\Nopeners.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.91,0:28:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Neverything therefore is relative is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.76,0:28:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,significant depends on how you\Ncontextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.24,0:28:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We all um are grateful and thankful that\Nwe are on a spiritual pathway. That is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.08,0:28:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the most difficult task of all that\Npeople think in terms of calibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.24,0:28:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the the calibration these are just\Nthe automatic consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.03,0:28:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you head due east and keep your\Ncompass in this direction, sooner or
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.20,0:28:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,later you're going to pass this island\Nand that that island and eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.72,0:28:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to get your goal. The\Nhardest thing about all of spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.12,0:28:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is to get your compass set on a\Nspiritual goal. 85% of the population
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.72,0:28:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sneers at it, right? It's just\Nridiculous. It's absurd and etc. To even
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.24,0:28:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,be on the spiritual pathway is already\Nthe greatest karma there is. That is the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.72,0:29:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest gift. The rest is automatic\Nbecause once you get bit by the bug,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.15,0:29:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have much choice about it.\NOnce you get bit by the spiritual bug,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.79,0:29:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the way home is certain. You know, you\Nmay get lost here and there for a few
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.12,0:29:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes or wandering around. But\Nthat's irrelevant
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.72,0:29:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because the the pathway is going to pull\Nyou. So we said you're not propelled by
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.60,0:29:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,your past, you're attracted by your\Nfuture. And you set your future by your
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.20,0:29:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,choice and design and by your spiritual\Nagreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.76,0:29:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens then? And of course in\Nquantum mechanics, you know, there's no
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.76,0:29:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,past, present or future.\NThere is no such a thing as a sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.24,0:29:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of past, present, and future. In the\Ninfinite quantum potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.96,0:30:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the future precedes the present.\NYou understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.27,0:30:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you've already chosen the future\Nand activated it in the now. The future
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.12,0:30:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's acting activating you now.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.15,0:30:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\NSo everyone here is being pulled by the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.15,0:30:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite potentiality which you have\Nalready chosen and committed to or you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.32,0:30:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be here.\NYou'd be at the ball game.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.76,0:30:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So everyone should relax that the way is\Ncertain. Enlightenment is certain for
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.03,0:30:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody here or you wouldn't be here.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.44,0:30:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The future then is what is activating\Nyou in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.64,0:30:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? That make sense now?\N>> Because of what you've already chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.55,0:30:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already chosen that out of the\Nquantum potentiality. You have an
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.84,0:31:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite number of choices. But you've\Nchosen that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.96,0:31:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That is now what is attracting you. like\Na magnet to the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.00,0:31:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,dragging you through all that you have\Nto go through,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.76,0:31:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,giving up chocolate and everything.\NI gave up chocolate for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.27,0:31:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's I got this halo.\NI remember when I gave up chocolate for
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.39,0:31:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NTotally let it go. Thank God it was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.91,0:31:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,gone.\NI was free as a bird. I never thought of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.76,0:31:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,chocolate. I didn't want chocolate. The\Nheck with chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.27,0:31:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I had a whole bunch of people out from\Nthe course of miracles to a place that I
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.91,0:31:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was staying at at the time and big\Nplace. And guess what? They brought
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.12,0:31:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,big sheet cakes of chocolate cake.\NChocolate. I had chocolate everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.32,0:32:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When I didn't want chocolate, didn't\Nneed chocolate. Couldn't care less about
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.51,0:32:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,chocolate.\NAnd I've lived in a chocolate world ever
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.84,0:32:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,since. So\NI don't need or want chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.60,0:32:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the side boy at home. There's three\Nor four different kinds of chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.20,0:32:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And guess what Miss Lovely made for me\Nthis weekend?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.24,0:32:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Chocolate fudge.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.39,0:32:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what you let go of comes comes into you.\NAnd and that's the trouble with
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.51,0:32:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,abundance. You see\Nthat's the trouble with abundance is uh
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.76,0:32:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when you don't want anything anymore\Nthere there it just pours in from all
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.24,0:33:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,over.\NOkay. So, this question has arisen
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.20,0:33:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,before. I think I already answered it\Nearlier today that the ego can grab on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.84,0:33:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to the numeric scale and think, well,\NI'm 480 and they're 460, so I'm better.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.79,0:33:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, the ego can do that with\Nanything. And it does do that with
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.20,0:33:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,everything all the time. That's the\Nquality of the ego, which you then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.12,0:33:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,project onto everything. And of course\Nwe can do it on a scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.72,0:33:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can do it on anything else. So\Nthat's just a propensity of the of the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.39,0:33:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ego and one of the things we have to\Nrelinquish is the desire to be better
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.36,0:33:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,than others because\Nthere is no such thing and better in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.91,0:33:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what meaning of the word better etc.\NOkay. Are there spiritual differences
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.84,0:33:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,between men and women?\NOh my, this is a damn
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.67,0:34:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,leave this one right there.\NOh, here was a springer. Honey, did you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.48,0:34:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,know this was in here?\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.07,0:34:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay,\N>> I'm allowed to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.04,0:34:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There are spiritual differences between\Nmen and women. He said, "No, no
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.39,0:34:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,differences."\NNot. Yeah. You know, the essential
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.00,0:34:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,reality obviously would have to be the\Nsame. However, the way they manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.20,0:34:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be perhaps different because it\Nreflects cultural influences.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.56,0:34:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It is permissible in our culture for\Nwomen to be intuitive
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.72,0:34:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to call upon the nonlinear side of their\Nawareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.87,0:35:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not so okay for men to do that.\NIs not so okay. And um
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.92,0:35:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a man has to be somewhat more evolved to\Ngive himself permission
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.44,0:35:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh to call upon his intuitive side, you\Nknow. So in our culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.88,0:35:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the woman is more free to be intuitive\Nand therefore she perfects perfects that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.28,0:35:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,side. I think she perfects that side.\NAs a psychiatrist, I'm speaking now. She
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.80,0:35:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,perfects that side\Nbefore the man does.
